{
  "stem": "4284.4",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 150,
      "text": "There was all kinds of things that they could organize.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 151,
      "text": "They just went down the hill, mountain, brought back cattle, slaughtered it, cooked it in the kitchen, which did exist.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 152,
      "text": "And everybody had a feast and promptly died from the inability to absorb food.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 153,
      "text": "And again, very fortunate, the younger ones, having been taken care of by the Red Cross, ended up getting very little food because they sort of gradually fed us, not to have the tragedy of dying because of inability to assimilate food into our bodies, which had been undernourished for years, and in the last 10 or so days, totally incapacitated to make any kind of absorption of the food.",
      "word_count": 70
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 154,
      "text": "So these people died because of food.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "To me personally, we were now in a terrible position.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had been liberated, something I had looked forward to for four and 1/2 years.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the next thing is a new worry.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "What next?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "What to do?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Well, the Red Cross took names and disseminated the list of survivors all over the world.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Jewish organization, the German-speaking paper in Los Angeles called the And they quickly listed the survivors that they found in all the camps.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We didn't know what would happen.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I refused to go back to Germany.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I had no way-- I did not-- the slightest idea what to do.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So we hung around, literally.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We were planning something.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We were going back to the-- to Poland and to-- one fellow was from Austria, Hungary, a lot of them.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But you just didn't know what to do.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The Red Cross said, you know, the juveniles, of which there were 400, will be divided between England, France, and Switzerland, and no particular choice given.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It just-- I was designated to go to France.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
